DialogueNode.dialogue: Hey, Dave.
Hey, Alex!
How's your day going so far?
Could we talk more about those reports I mentioned?
Oh. Yeah, sure.
Pretty average. To be honest, I'm pretty exhausted today. Thanks for asking though. Knowing someone cares brightens my day.
Of course!
Hey, by the way. I know it's not super comfortable, but are you okay revisiting our conversation from yesterday?
Yeah, that'd be alright.
Is there anything else you can tell me? I really want to help make this office a better place, but I need some help to do that.
Well, you know... I have noticed some things. Like, in meetings I noticed that Stan tends to kind of... steamroll some of the female employees.
He never really seems to listen to them. And there was this one time when... Uh... Never mind
What were you about to say? Please, Dave. If you think it's useful information, I can use it to potentially help the women in this office feel safer and more comfortable.
Thanks, Dave. This has been very helpful.
Well . . . Okay. I trust you're here to help, Alex.
The other day Stan totally blew up at Sharon. He told her that she needs to stop letting her "hormones interfere with her work."
She was so embarrassed... She left early.
Thank you so much for sharing this with me, Dave. I promise, the appropriate action will be taken. You've helped a lot of people today.
Anytime. Let me know if there's anything else I can do to help. I really would like to see this office become a better place.
Me too, Dave. And it's going to be.
